
[1]aft

   'AFT, a. or adv.

   In seaman's language, a word used to denote the stern or what pertains
   to the stern of a ship; as, the aft part of the ship; haul aft the main
   sheet, that is, further towards the stern. Fore and aft is the whole
   length of a ship. Right aft is in a direct line with the stern.
